In JavaScript, you create a subclass using the `class` syntax with the `extends` keyword. Here's a simple example compared to Python:

**JavaScript:**
```javascript
class Parent {
  constructor(name) {
    this.name = name;
  }
}

class Child extends Parent {
  constructor(name, age) {
    super(name);  // Call parent constructor
    this.age = age;
  }
}

const obj = new Child("Alice", 25);
```

**Python:**
```python
