    def __init__(self, name):
        self.name = name

class Child(Parent):
    def __init__(self, name, age):
        super().__init__(name)
        self.age = age

obj = Child("Alice", 25)
```

Key differences:
1. JavaScript uses `extends` instead of parentheses
2. JavaScript requires `super()` call before using `this`
3. JavaScript constructors use the `constructor` keyword instead of `__init__`

