1. Takes two arrays as input
2. Creates a result array with maximum possible size (minimum of the two input sizes)
3. Checks each element of the first array against all elements of the second array
4. Adds common elements to the result array, avoiding duplicates
5. Returns the intersection array along with its size
6. The main function demonstrates usage with example arrays

